modules.description: Handles file descriptor operations such as reading, writing, and closing, along with non-blocking I/O setup. Works with file descriptors, byte arrays, and Unix process identifiers. Used to manage asynchronous communication between processes and to implement custom I/O handlers in networked applications.

Provides functions to retrieve and manipulate timezone data, including conversion between timezone names and their corresponding identifiers. Works with lists of tuples containing timezone names and identifiers. Used to generate lookup tables for system timezone mappings in applications requiring locale-specific time handling.
